741
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:23,400
We can do business.

742
00:52:26,900 --> 00:52:30,900
That's it. One-two, one-two, one-two.

743
00:52:31,600 --> 00:52:35,200
One-two, that's it. One-two, there you go.

744
00:52:35,700 --> 00:52:40,000
All right, there it is. Now you getting it.
Keep that left hand up.

745
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:49,800
All right. Watch your balance now.
Don't lean forward.

746
00:52:49,900 --> 00:52:52,000
Don't lean too much.
Don't lean too forward, all right?

747
00:52:52,100 --> 00:52:54,800
All right, let's go.
Don't lean too forward, that's right.

748
00:52:54,900 --> 00:52:55,900
One-two, pivot.

749
00:52:56,300 --> 00:53:00,200
You're kidding. Tell me he's kidding.

750
00:53:01,600 --> 00:53:03,500
You're kidding, right?

751
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:08,300
- He did it without our knowledge.
- Without your knowledge.

752
00:53:08,700 --> 00:53:11,100
Well, that's worse.
You're the Commissioner.

753
00:53:11,300 --> 00:53:13,100
Was the Commissioner.

754
00:53:13,600 --> 00:53:16,900
You think the buck's gonna stop
in this office, you're wrong.

755
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:18,500
If I might...

756
00:53:19,400 --> 00:53:22,500
these are letters from people in his district.

757
00:53:22,900 --> 00:53:25,800
Ministers, business people, voters.

758
00:53:26,400 --> 00:53:28,200
All glowing reports.

759
00:53:28,400 --> 00:53:32,700
And there's the 14% reduction in crime
in the Western.

760
00:53:33,500 --> 00:53:37,500
That's not an anomaly. It's hard data.

761
00:53:38,600 --> 00:53:41,400
Now, we can clean it up, make it go away.

762
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:44,900
The press might already have wind of it,
but we can explain that...

763
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:47,700
as some sort of a new initiative.

764
00:53:48,400 --> 00:53:50,400
Trap high-end drug dealers.

765
00:53:51,500 --> 00:53:52,700
14%.

766
00:53:53,800 --> 00:53:58,300
If we handle this right,
we might all get out from underneath.

767
00:53:58,500 --> 00:54:00,100
No mud on anybody.

768
00:54:02,800 --> 00:54:04,500
No. No.

769
00:54:06,000 --> 00:54:08,800
I trusted you, Erv, I really did.

770
00:54:08,900 --> 00:54:10,400
You let me down.

771
00:54:10,800 --> 00:54:13,100
Now, this thing goes wrong,
no telling the damage.

772
00:54:13,200 --> 00:54:14,700
On this, you walk point.

773
00:54:14,800 --> 00:54:18,200
That's the way things work, Erv.
You know it as well as I do.

774
00:54:24,400 --> 00:54:26,000
Thank you, Ervin.

775
00:54:27,000 --> 00:54:28,000
I'll be over shortly...

776
00:54:28,100 --> 00:54:32,200
to see the detailed plan on
how this shit gets cleaned up immediately.

777
00:54:48,500 --> 00:54:51,800
If you could call this shit
something other than what it <i>is...</i>

778
00:54:51,900 --> 00:54:53,600
Don't even think it.

779
00:54:59,400 --> 00:55:00,700
The way it works is this.

780
00:55:00,800 --> 00:55:04,300
If you don't re-up the minutes
on your cell phone before 60 days...

781
00:55:04,400 --> 00:55:06,500
the wireless company recycles
the phone numbers.

782
00:55:06,600 --> 00:55:08,200
And that's where I get them.

783
00:55:08,300 --> 00:55:11,200
I put the word out on the street
that I'm buying tossed-off burners...

784
00:55:11,300 --> 00:55:12,700
paying $2 a pop.

785
00:55:12,800 --> 00:55:14,700
Street people bring me hundreds.

786
00:55:14,800 --> 00:55:17,300
I bring them in here to my niece,
she jiggles the computer...

787
00:55:17,400 --> 00:55:20,700
juices them up another 200 minutes
on a bogus account.

788
00:55:20,900 --> 00:55:25,400
And that automatically extends
the life of the phone for another 60 days.

789
00:55:25,700 --> 00:55:28,300
She charges me $20 on each phone
on her end.

790
00:55:28,400 --> 00:55:31,300
I double it or more on the street
to make mine.

791
00:55:31,400 --> 00:55:33,100
So what you saying?

792
00:55:33,600 --> 00:55:36,900
Baby, a standard Tracfone with 200,
maybe 400 minutes on it...

793
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:38,900
gonna run you $150, $200 easy.

794
00:55:39,400 --> 00:55:43,300
I charge you an even $100.
You clear $50 on each phone.

795
00:55:43,400 --> 00:55:45,600
That's if you can back them up
with receipts.

796
00:55:45,700 --> 00:55:49,900
I gotta show receipts looking like
they from different places, or I can't play.

797
00:55:50,700 --> 00:55:52,700
Can we accommodate the good man?

798
00:55:52,800 --> 00:55:55,800
Damn, Calvin,
you know I got the bingo tonight.

799
00:56:07,800 --> 00:56:10,300
Look, friend,
I ain't sure you wanna be around here...

800
00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:13,700
and I'm damn sure we're getting
tired of having you. That plain enough?

801
00:56:13,800 --> 00:56:17,200
You should know by now, I don't wanna be
around no bunch of cocksucking faggots.

802
00:56:17,300 --> 00:56:19,700
But I ain't gonna stop coming round
till I run up on Omar.

803
00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:21,400
You might want to get the word out.

804
00:56:21,500 --> 00:56:23,700
For the last time, I don't know him.

805
00:56:23,800 --> 00:56:25,500
Then I'm back tomorrow.

806
00:56:50,100 --> 00:56:51,600
Maybe I can help you?

807
00:56:56,600 --> 00:56:58,800
I don't doubt it for a minute.

